                    <p>
                        ii.Cloudy: This is when the clouds cover the sunlight.
                        <a href="#!"><img class="img-fluid" src="/images/cloudy.png" alt="..." /></a><span class="caption text-muted">Here we can see children having fun in the sunny weather</span></p>

                        <p>
                            iii.Rainy: Rain is droplets of water that fall from the clouds.
                            <a href="#!"><img class="img-fluid" src="/images/rainy.png" alt="..." /></a>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            iv.Windy: This is when air moves quickly enough for you to feel it on your face.
                            <a href="#!"><img class="img-fluid" src="/images/windy.png" alt="..." /></a>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            v.Stormy: This is when there is a strong wind, lightning, thunder and heavy rain.
                            <a href="#!"><img class="img-fluid" src="/images/stormy.png" alt="..." /></a>
                        </p>

                        <p>
                            vi.Snowy: When the air is cold, water droplets in the clouds freeze into ice crystals.
                            <a href="#!"><img class="img-fluid" src="/images/snowy.png" alt="..." /></a>
                        </p>
